Do the following when matplot lib doesn't run on your Mac OS X device.

change your directory to the following

$ cd ~/.matplotlib

Then, nano matplotlibrc file as follows
$ nano matplotlibrc

Inside this file, insert the following text,
backend: TkAgg

use ctrl+C to exit and type y to exit and return to exit to save the file with the same name.

Finally, to plot graphs or images in matplotlib, import in your python program as follows

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
